# Portfolio Domain Rules

## Pages
- `pages/index.vue` — single-page portfolio with all sections
- `pages/projects/[slug].vue` — individual project detail page
- `pages/uses.vue` — optional /uses page (tools & setup)

## Required Sections (in order on index page)
1. `HeroSection` — name, title, CTA buttons, social links
2. `AboutSection` — bio, photo, skills overview
3. `ProjectsSection` — project cards grid
4. `SkillsSection` — skill categories with icons/levels
5. `ExperienceSection` — timeline of work history
6. `ContactSection` — contact form or mailto CTA

## Project Data Shape
```ts
interface Project {
  slug: string
  title: string
  description: string
  tags: string[]          // e.g. ['Vue 3', 'Nuxt', 'TypeScript']
  liveUrl?: string
  repoUrl?: string
  coverImage: string      // path relative to public/images/
  featured: boolean
  year: number
}
```

## SEO
- Every page must have `useSeoMeta()` with `title`, `description`, `ogImage`, `ogTitle`
- Use `definePageMeta()` for layout assignment
- All images need descriptive `alt` text
- Semantic HTML: `<header>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<footer>`

## Accessibility
- Color contrast ratio: minimum 4.5:1 for body text, 3:1 for large text
- All interactive elements must be keyboard-navigable
- Focus styles must be visible — never `outline: none` without a replacement
- Icons used as buttons need `aria-label`

## Performance
- Images: use Nuxt `<NuxtImg>` (nuxt/image) — never raw `<img>` for content images
- Lazy load sections below the fold with `v-intersection-observer` or native `loading="lazy"`
- No blocking scripts in `<head>`
